<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8">
		<title>BA Stundenplan2CAL</title>
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
		<meta name="description" content="">
		<meta name="author" content="">
		<%= stylesheet_link_tag    "application", :media => "all" %>
		<!-- HTML5 shim, for IE6-8 support of HTML5 elements -->
		<!--[if lt IE 9]>
		<script src="http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"></script>
		<![endif]-->
		<%= javascript_include_tag "application" %>
		<%= csrf_meta_tags %>

		<!-- Fav and touch icons -->
		<link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" sizes="144x144" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-144-precomposed.png">
		<link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" sizes="114x114" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-114-precomposed.png">
		<link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" sizes="72x72" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-72-precomposed.png">
		<link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-57-precomposed.png">
		<link rel="shortcut icon" href="../assets/ico/favicon.png">
	</head>

	<body>
		<%= render "layouts/fb_sdk"%>
		<div class="container-narrow">

			<%= render "layouts/header"%>

			<hr>

			<div class="jumbotron">
				<h1>Stundenplan einfach exportieren?</h1>
				<p class="lead">
					Nach dem Motto: "Not macht erfinderisch", stellt diese App die bisher fehlende/fehlerhafte Funktion im Self-Service-Portal, den Stundenplan für Outlook, Google Calendar, iCal etc. zu exportieren, zur Verfügung.
				</p>
				<div id="main-content" class="span5">
					<%= bootstrap_flash %>
					<%= yield %>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr>

			<div id="comments" class="row-fluid marketing">
				<div class="span12">
					<h2>Kommentare</h2>
					<br />
					<%= render "layouts/fb_comments"%>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr>

			<%= render "layouts/footer"%>

		</div>
		<!-- /container -->

	</body>
</html>